} // Uncaught SyntaxError: Rest parameter must be last formal parameter

doWork("John", 1, 2, 3, 4, "doe"); 

Rest operator is part of function defination.

Spread operator
===============
spread is negation to Rest.

Rest operator take individual values and combine them into an array. Spread operator take an array and split it into individual values.

Spread operator is part of the function calling statement or other.

let doWork = function(x, y, z){
  console.log(x);
  console.log(y);
  console.log(z);
}

let arr = [1,2,3];
doWork(...arr);
doWork(...[4, 5, 6]);

build new arrays:
let a = [4,5,6];
let b = [1,2,3,...a,7,8,9];

we can also spread objects:
let obj = { food: "spicy", price: "$10", ambiance: "peaceful" };
let search = { ...obj, cuisine: "chinese" };

***** We can use spread operator to shallow clone an object.
let user = { name: 'John', age: 25 };
let userCopy = user;
let userShallowClone = { ...user };

user.age = 30; // We find the updated age in both 'user' and 'userCopy', but not in userShallowClone
userShallowClone.name = 'Michael'; // Only userShallowClone is updated. Not user or userCopy.

